reviews_data.review_text: Everything I need in one convenient location.
Very cute vibe. I stopped in for a espresso martini with reposado, it was delicious.

This is a hidden gem. We didn’t know anything about it going in but we’re immediately greeted by Mitchell and Steven who were bartending and they not only make a great drink but the food was incredible, they made it right behind the bar! The Italian sub was the best I’ve had in Charlotte and the espresso martini selection is perfect! We will make this a regular stop. They were so fun!
Mobetta Blues Thursdays 🫶🏾🤌🏿
Strange atmosphere. I get a bad vibe whenever I go there and weird older men kept asking me personal details about me and were being pushy and weird. Will not go back in that area
Good sandwich selection, chicken Caesar and chicken caprese were really good! Great lunch special as well!

I was aura maxing after a 5 mile run and decided to check this place out. I’ve heard about their chicken caesar wrap on instagram and had to check it out.

The hype was definitely worth it, this place is a gem. The guy work the counter was a real pimp on his own wellness journey, much respect for this fella. I really feel like you can’t miss here.

Once again, hypothetically if you locked me in here and filled the place to the ceiling with these wraps and forced me to eat my way out… I would need a minute, but I wouldn’t complain. The wrap left me with some tight plums and wanting more.  Will definitely be back.

I really love supporting small businesses like this. You know what really got me hard while I was there? The frozen section, took some stuffed shells home and the rest was history.

Went into the exchange , iv met the people that have a worked there for a minute and started a relationship, but I said I couldn’t hear them one night and   It completely changed, one night when I said I could not hear them over the music. I continued to ask “hey I can’t hear u can u hear me “ and it was a complete ignorance , so I continued cause i had known em , they said they be busy and I waited for a slower moment as a customer, the guys I hav known for months acted like it was nothing and didn’t wanna deal with a simple question like.    “Hey will u be open tmw?” They asked me to leave without any consideration.  won’t be going again. Iv shopped for a while too just not worth the people that work there honestly , Iv worked in service industry too and yet I have the patience for anyone
Great place to get beer and wine, and then get some to go. We like the location. Seeing my nieces  artwork, done for her good friend, makes this place  special.
Love the exchange! It’s the best spot in noda. Would be cooler they had kratom seltzer.
Love this place. The new outdoor patio is amazing.
Jamel  with Offline - Just good food and vibes

Shannon with Offline - I had the crunchwrap lunch combo for $12 and it came with a bag of chips and a can of soda. The crunchwrap was definitely better than Taco Bell but a little too spicy. I'd recommend getting without the jalapeños if you're not a fan of really spicy things. My boyfriend got the chicken parm sub and I tried it and it was really good!

Cute spot with friendly service - could see this being a cool spot to grab a drink with friends.

I tried the cold brew and wasn’t a fan, and I was charged extra for regular (dairy) milk, which I’m not used to seeing. The music was also a little loud (with noise cancelling headphones) so I won’t come back to do work here again, but would still give this place another try for drinks. The ladies working the bar were great.
The service is horrible, I witness 2 servers being extremely rude  to an elderly couple,  I left, I refuse to spend my money at this poor excuse of an establishment!
Quaint, chill bar and market in the heart of NoDa. Great variety of drinks from beers to martinis and everything in between.
Went to a class last night with Stephen to learn how to make three holiday cocktails.  So much fun-definitely recommend it if they have another!
Was working across the street at Industrious and Offfline brought me in! Pizza was good and the vibe was perfect for a mid-afternoon coworking session.
Nice staff. Small but that could be a good thing. Nice beer options and wings good. Will come back
Best damn sandwiches and wraps!   Visiting from Austin, Tx and luckily stumbled in and found a gem.  Wonder if I could DoorDash the 1200 miles.  Cool ownership and workers too.

Stopped by real quick to buy a bottle of wine. We were looking for a bottle of prosecco, but unfortunately, they did not have any. My friend ended up getting a sour beer. I saw they sold boxes of whiteclaw's, and I just wanted one, but they were so polite and got one for me from one of the boxes, which I truly appreciated. Ambiance was everything here. It was around 8 p.m., and it was super calm. Plans and chic decor everywhere. They have a bar with seating as well as a couple of lounge chairs and seating outside. Def recommend if you are in the area.

My friend & I had a fabulous time painting 2 of our favorite artists hosted by @iv_logan at @theexchangeclt! He hosts a “paint your artist sip n paint” every other Monday @7pm for $40 (glass of wine included). WHEN you go, make sure you have #Six make you one of his wonderful sangrias & the pork bbq nachos. Babyyyyy, both are delicious! Good vibes, friendly people, great food & drinks and reasonable prices! Can’t wait to go back🤗

Quaint little bar with absolutely amazing food! Our table got the Hot Italian and Buffalo Sliders. Ya'll it was delicious! There's a little convenient store inside with snacks, sweets, beer, and wine for sale to take with you. The small patio out back is dog friendly but they're is no table service out there.
Mitchell made me the best sandwich I’ve ever had in my life. Actually outstanding.
Kevin and his team are amazing, food drinks , atmosphere, and the location premium that guy knows what he's doing🔥🔥🔥🔥🔥👍👍👍👍
Peaceful and you feel right at home

I got the turkey melt wrap and it was delicious. Well worth the price. The Peru coffee I got tasted amazing as well.

Update: chicken caprese sandwich is delicious as well. A little messy to eat. Ask for a fork and knife.
Really not living up to its potential here. The bartender was only interested in pushing his trivia event rather than engaging in meaningful discourse
Their prices are “convenience” based and they have always been nice when I went in. It’s a basic store/bar with some essentials, alcohol, and small deli.
Always amazing music and polite staff! Being able to walk here from my apartment to get a drink, snack, or any household item is the greatest convenience!

The Exchange on 36th is a hidden gem in the NoDa area. The restaurant is also a small convenience store with awesome specialty items. I wanted to stay there with a good book or my iPad for hours. The atmosphere, food, drinks, staff were so welcoming! Kevin is the bartender of the year! He was so kind and he challenged me to step outside my comfort zone and try the pimentos in the blue cheese ( I ate the buffalo chicken sliders) they were simply dancing. Lastly I drank the Im”pare”Ed margarita and it was delicious! I give this place a 10 out of 10! & I will be returning!!
Always awesome!!!!❤️
Love family dollar
Wow, a hidden gem of a neighborhood bar! Drinks and food are equally fantastic!
Heart of Noda. Best drinks and place to hangout in the area!!
The drinks were good, the food was good, the vibes were classy. I felt cool being there.
The BEST Italian sandwich. Such a cool spot in NoDa and it was quiet on a Saturday afternoon for lunch. Love the beer and wine selection and all the Pasta & Provisions items available in the market.
Steven is the man!

Get the Italian. It's heavenly. I'm very passionate about sandwiches. I can talk at length about unwritten rules of sandwiches and how easy a sandwich is to get wrong. This place does NOT get it wrong. Aside from the modern ambiance and friendly service (shout out to Six) the sandwiches rise to meet and exceed my expectations. The exchange is quickly becoming my favorite lunch stop (and beer stop). Pictured is the turkey melt. Not as good as the Italian but still great.

They have a small selection of groceries that include pasta and provisions.
Great little spot to pick up drinks, snacks, & a quick bite to eat. Staff is friendly. Diverse crowd which makes it even better.
Cool spot! Friendly staff and an awesome Jarritos Paloma

I hate to leave a bad review, but it was a no for me! Bathroom sink was broken. So hot in there that I couldn't even attempt to enjoy anything. Customer service, I don't even know how to even describe it. Not one table was wiped off the entire time I was there. My advice is to welcome people, especially, individuals that have never been there. Parking is a nightmare. The public parking is sky high. One was $4 for every 30 minutes or $28 for the day. It is a cool concept, I guess, but I didn't enjoy it all. Actually, I was upset that I wasted 40 minutes to go there.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Snow. I am sorry you had a bad experience today. It is almost 100 degrees out today as well as yesterday so it is hard for HVAC systems to keep up in this sort of heat. As far as the broken sink, it is automatic and you just needed to place your hands under the faucet to turn on. It was also very busy in there at that time and can take a minute for employees to get over to wipe off tables especially when there is a line at the counter and only a couple of open seats in the establishment. Parking, you are more than welcome to take that up with the city as we have no say so as to the prices they charge. I hope you are willing to come back and give us a try when it is not the hottest day of the year and a packed house which only creates more heat. I am sorry you spent 40 minutes getting here. My suggestion would be to go out during the week and not the weekends in noda especially during busy hours as most places around you will find will be at least 90% full making it hard for employees to judge who has been there or not to drop everything to say hello when a new guest walks in. Thank you for our first one star review. It is very humbling.

reviews_data.review_text: If I lived in NoDa, this is where I would be a local.  Chill vibe.  Good beer.  Nice staff.  Indoor and outdoor seating
Great food, drink and service!!! Get the Italian and thank me later.
Friendly place to have a pint. Nice selections of adult beverages. Indoor and outdoor seating. Our first visit, so we will try to come back and post more details.
Laid back but very fun
Awesome hidden spot in a cool part of Charlotte (NoDa). Chicken Caesar wrap was amazing and great selection of cocktails and beers (drafts and cans).

Very cool hang out.
Have nice quick bar food
And plenty of different beers ,wines and liquors.

I have passed this place plenty and thought it was another lil bar. Man was I wrong. I went in abt 1:30 on a Thursday and was pleasantly surprised at how cute and quaint it was. It has a lil store section to buy sodas, beer, snacks etch, but they also have food you can order and eat there. I tried the hot Italian and my God! I can’t even begin to describe to y’all the deliciousness factor.

When the food was brought out the man (who I found out later was the owner) asked me “are you ready to try your new addiction? Of course at first I was like yea ok I’m sure it ain’t all that, lol….well paint my face with embarrassment cuz that sandwich was sandwiching! Lol. The bread was crunchy yet not hard to eat, the sandwich was hot and juicy and the flavors all coming together was insanity. I literally have found my new addiction that’s for sure! Lol. And the sandwich, chips and soda was only $13 during their lunch special hours that end at 2pm. I can’t recommend this place enough!

Dipped into this spot because of a rain storm while walking through NODA and I'm glad we did. Got a drink and a snack while we waited for the rain to pass on a Sunday early afternoon, and it was really a nice little spot. They have a small market for the essentials, beer on tap and wine by the glass, and it looked like they had a full menu for sandwiches and other in-house food. Staff was nice, too.
Great vibe, awesome staff, great food and drinks! Their bubbles on tap are the best I’ve ever had.

I was In trouble and was stranded.  I went to  7 businesses in Noda to ask for help getting home. I was willing to work. Each place treated me awful.  Especially the business at corner of  36th and Plaza rd. The bartender here was AMAZING. He gave me his only tips yo help me. No hesitation.  This business is 5 star because of the equal treatment unlike the other places in Noda that treated me bad because I was black
I love this place. Come here. Seriously - it will be the highlight of your night
Quaint and casual. I did not put it together until I showed up that they also sell convenience store items. Sandwiches were just the right thing.
Food is amazing, atmosphere is out of this world, and the customer service here can’t be beat!
Great  place  to  get a drink  and chill...." chai to meet you " the drink  was off  the  change get it lol off the EXCHANGE..

Charlottes #1 bodega bar and grill! Great little store with tons of unique local offerings in addition to standard convenience store items. Relaxed atmosphere with great music and friendly service. They have an expanding food menu now too and I haven’t found anything I didn’t like. Great place to just relax and have a couple beers and some food. Cant recommend it enough.
Unique cocktails, food, and convenience store items all in one spot. A great little neighborhood shop!

Wonderful neighbor bar and market. The bartender is fabulous and extremely personable. Delicious drinks. I will certainly be back to visit again soon. Highly recommend the locally made desserts sold here. Yum!
immaculate vibes
This is the best GO-TO Spot ! From Cash & Carry to a quick Mimosa at the Bar!!!  The fact that they are a Private Club now is even MORE amazing!!
Cool laid back spot

When in Noda, please stop by. Great little neighborhood bar and market. The limited menu has an eclectic vibe and I highly recommend the spam sliders. Who knew spam could be so good when served with pimento cheese? The bartender made great recommendations for other places in the area to visit. The market is great for picking up that bottle of wine you need for dinner, too.
Came to the Exchange after being turned away from two other bars who were reservation only. We were greeted with a smile and served right away. There’s hope for the Queen City after all

Truly one of the best spots to go AM or PM Feeds the soul!  I’ve picked up great wine , had lovely conversations and found my new favorite soy candle company through the exchange. Thank you for having the most beautiful place.

Had pancakes there this morning.
They were excellent. Highly recommend giving them a try.

Great local market in NoDa! I go here somewhat frequently as it's walkable from many of the apartments in the area, they have really good local products, my favorite being the chocolate milk from a North Carolina dairy farm!

Oh and it's also a super fun looking wine bar at night, I'll have to try some of their wines one of these days

Super dope spot. The layout is very chic and well organized. Hella clutch when you're just wanting a quick beverage or something to snack on while you're walking around checking out the vendors. I would spot here first then walk around the neighborhood.

Love this place. Amazing staff, good selection of beer on tap and in the coolers. Yummy local treats, houseplants, coffee and fun snacks. Love the atmosphere and decor, too. If I lived closer, I would be there all the time.

Great local market in NoDa! I go here somewhat frequently as it's walkable from many of the apartments in the area, they have really good local products, my favorite being the chocolate milk from a North Carolina dairy farm!

Oh and it's also a super fun looking wine bar at night, I'll have to try some of their wines one of these days

Super dope spot. The layout is very chic and well organized. Hella clutch when you're just wanting a quick beverage or something to snack on while you're walking around checking out the vendors. I would spot here first then walk around the neighborhood.

Love this place. Amazing staff, good selection of beer on tap and in the coolers. Yummy local treats, houseplants, coffee and fun snacks. Love the atmosphere and decor, too. If I lived closer, I would be there all the time.
